@nfunwigabga, @cheninformz 
We can down version to resolve this issue, the exact version is `"exceljs": "1.12.0"`
I try it and it's work pretty perfectly

If you create ExcelJS.Workbook is read a file that already exists. Maby excel row or column used the same style instance. so, you modify style is global. You can:
```javascript
worksheet.getCell('A1').font = { ...worksheet.getCell('A1').font}
worksheet.getCell('A1').font. color = { argb: '3a80d5' }
```

Okay for someone who step in to this situation i can fix by using this method
            sheet.getCell(`F22`).value = {
                 richText: [{ font: { size: 12, color: { argb: "FFFF6600" }, name: "Calibri", scheme: "minor" }, text: `Text here` }],
             };
